article.headline: Brown 67, Yale 62
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Marcus Becker scored 18 points and Brown converted 17 turnovers into 26 points for a 67-62 victory over Yale on Saturday. Becker scored seven consecutive points at the end of a 14-0 run in the first half as Brown built a 28-19 lead that it never gave up. Damon Huffman added 15 points and Mark MacDonald scored 11 as the Bears (5-10, 1-1 Ivy League) won their first home game of the season after five losses. Eric Flato had 13 points for the Bulldogs (9-8, 1-1), who lost to Brown for the seventh time in the last eight meetings between the teams. Sam Kaplan added 11. Yale led 16-9 when MacDonald made a short jump shot that ignited the 14-0 run. Becker scored two free throws, a fast break layup and a 3-point shot in the run. Brown led 39-30 at halftime and went on a 10-0 run early in the second half, keyed a pair of 3-point baskets by Huffman, to take the largest lead of the game 58-40 with 10:51 left.
